rows.<DBAF43F0>:
Fighting for Colony 9, Noah, Lanz, Eunie and Mwamba
go toe-to-toe in battle with soldiers from Colony Sigma.
Then, once the dust settles...

With their eyes set on Swordmarch,
Noah and co. decide to head south
through the Aetia region.

With the Flame Clock now destroyed,
Noah and co. have a few things
they need to do around Colony 4.

Departing Colony Lambda, Noah
and co. once again set their sights
on reaching Swordmarch.

The party escapes the Castle, with
Swordmarch now within reach.
Noah gets lost, grasping amidst the fog...

Noah learns about Moebius and Ouroboros
from Queen Nia. The time has finally come
to confront Z.

Once sworn enemies, Noah's and Mio's parties
join forces in order to survive, and set out on
the long journey toward Swordmarch.

Noah and co. destroy the Colony 4 Flame Clock,
and discover that the Consuls and Moebius are
one and the same.

Driving away Joran, who is now a Moebius,
the party destroy Colony Lambda's Flame Clock.

The Annihilator is destroyed, and the safety of
Colony 4 assured, but the Queen of Keves is
revealed to be a mechanical fake.

Two Moebius resembling Noah and Mio overpower
the party and imprison them in the Castle, where
Mio is forced to await her Coming-of-Age...

The party settle matters with Joran and D once
and for all, and finally get to meet the true
Queen of Agnus face-to-face.

The two worlds, once forced into stasis,
begin once more to speed toward their
respective futures...

Defeat the Colony Sigma soldiers
standing in your way.

Navigate the battlefield to reach
the Colony Sigma Iron Giant.

Defeat the Colony Sigma soldiers
standing in your way.

Navigate the battlefield to reach
the Colony Sigma Iron Giant.

Defeat the Colony Sigma soldiers
standing in your way.

Defeat the Colony Sigma Ulula
Levnis.

Head to the bathing tent,
and have a bath.

Return to your barracks, and get
some rest.

Pass through the Colony 9 Iron Giant
to get to the assembly square.

Level up at the Forward Post
Camp, and prepare for battle.

Progress through Alfeto Valley and
investigate the objective.

Progress through Alfeto Valley
while remaining undetected.

Reach the mysterious ether source
that crash landed into Alfeto Valley.

Drive away the attacking Agnus
army.

Reach the mysterious ether source
that crash landed into Alfeto Valley.

Reach the mysterious ether source
that crash landed into Alfeto Valley.

Drive away the three Agnian
soldiers.

There's no going back to Colony
Gamma. For now, head elsewhere.

Fight the ambushing Colony Gamma
soldier.

Check the container and see if it
contains any useful items.

Rest up at the Hillside
Iron Giant Hulk.

Head south of Aetia and test your
powers on some Bodom Grebels.

Go south through the Aetia region,
and enter the Fornis region.

Go south through the Eagus
Wilderness.

Head for the Colony 4 Iron Giant
to speak with Ethel.
Rest up at the Colony 4 Barracks.

Climb the cliff near Elsie's Spout,
then head south-east.

Head to the south-east of the
Fornis region.
Rest up at the Seilas Terrace Camp.

Reach the tunnels in the Pentelas
region.

Reach the underground river in the
Invidian Tunnels.
Defeat the Colony Lambda Iron Giant.
Pass through the Great Conté Falls.
Rest up at the Titan Rock Camp.

Descend down the Old Cliffside
Way.

Rest up at the Sparkling Pool
Camp.
Return to the Sparkling Pool Camp.

Pass through Morukuna Wildwood,
and reach the Castle.

Reach the container at the Castle's
back entrance.

Defeat Moebius, and destroy the
Annihilator.

Head to the Cadensia region, and
reach the Great Sword.
Reach the base of the Great Sword.

Talk to the residential guard, then
rest up.
Return to the Lost Numbers Dorm.

Rest at the Inlet Camp, and prepare
to infiltrate the prison camp.
Infiltrate the Li Garte Prison Camp.
Return to Cell No. 1 and rest up.

Rendezvous with Ghondor at
Watchtower No. 1.

Work with Ghondor to
defeat the reinforcements.
Find a way to escape the Castle.

Pass through the West Perimeter
Gate and reach Hope's Rest.
Rest up at the Station Breakroom.

Head for Captocorn Peak, where the
Cloudkeep and Colony Omega are.

Head for the Cloudkeep and Colony
Omega, found at Captocorn Peak.

Go through Captocorn Peak, and
reach the Cloudkeep.

Progress through the Cloudkeep
to meet the true Queen.

Head to Farview Cape in the
Erythia Sea.

Drive away the center defense
team.

Use the G you got from the Colony Sigma
operation to buy and equip a new
accessory for Noah.

Using his Collectopaedia Card, the party handed over
the things that Roald asked for. This should help with
provisioning the upcoming operation.

Go and talk to Camilla at the
Colony 9 Assembly Square.

Buy a Bronze Temple Guard from
Camilla.

Have Noah equip your new
Bronze Temple Guard.

Register the collected materials
onto Roald's Collectopaedia Card.

The party finds a decrepit Iron Giant
on their travels. Search it to see if
it contains any useful resources.

Using the filled ether cylinders, the
party rebooted the dilapidated machine and
claimed its treasures for themselves.

Go to the ether channel and harvest
some ether.

Return to the Iron Giant hulk,
and insert the ether cylinder.

Now that you've set up camp at
the oasis for the night, help
Manana make a scrumptious meal.

Cooking with Manana and gem crafting with Riku
are going to come in very handy for your
adventure. Don't neglect either.

Cook up a meal at the Lake
Rezzento Camp.
Return to the Lake Rezzento Camp.

Craft a gem at the Lake Rezzento
Camp.

With the southward route blocked and roadworks
ongoing, now's as good a time as any to see who
might need helping in Colony 4.

Colony 4 is revealed to be suffering from
a shortage of medical supplies, but Taion
seems to have a solution in mind.

Discuss Colony 4's issues at the
canteen.

While they slept, the party's stored provisions
were stolen by Tirkins. Search the nearby area
for ways to replenish the supplies.

The party gathered up a healthy
amount of provisions. Return to the
Sparkling Pool Camp.

Ghondor, currently in Agnian custody, knows
the location of the true Queens. The first step in
the prison rescue is talking to Samon in engineering.

Using the ether cylinders you brought him,
Samon embarks on a night of feverish work
to make sure the Boundary's usable by morning.

Before beginning the prison rescue operation,
you'll first need to talk to Kisame in Vinisog Holm.
Board the Boundary and set out to the Erythia Sea.

The plan to infiltrate the prison camp
and rescue Ghondor is now all set.
Head to the Inlet Camp first.

Rendezvous with the Lost Numbers
soldier at Vinisog Holm.
Collect intel on the prison camp.

At Vinisog Holm Camp, discuss
"Li Garte Prison Information".

The first day of incarceration sees the party
assigned to gathering food. Follow the warden's
orders, and keep your heads down.

The party survived their first day of prison
labor. There's nothing left to do but take it
easy and rest up for tomorrow.

Today, the party is sent to subjugate an
enraged Feris. Whoever succeeds will be
excused from other tasks, so get subjugating!

Though Ghondor had to help them prove it,
the party subjugated an enraged Feris, and
finished their second day of prison.

Take back some evidence that you
took down the Basreek Feris.

The guard has taken a shine to the party,
and shows it by giving them yet more work
to do. Hang tight till Ghondor gives the cue.

The breakout operation has finally begun.
Battle through the guards as you head for
Watchtower No. 1 to rendezvous with Ghondor.

Find Origin metal from across Aionios
to finish the ultimate vessel, and
conquer the Great Sea's vortex.

Bravery, the ultimate vessel, is now complete.
When you're ready to embark for Origin,
head to Farview Cape.

From out of nowhere, a mysterious
Levnis materializes, blocking the
way of the party.

The mysterious Levnis has disappeared,
returning whence it came. But what is the
significance of its arrival in the first place...?

In search of the last Origin metal,
the party head to Gardin Defense
Base, which is east of Keves Castle.

After battling and defeating Consul Crys,
the party acquire the last Origin metal.

It appears Colony 5, now at Gold
rank, can't be contacted. Meet up
with Bolearis and investigate.

It turns out colony ranks were devised by
Moebius to stoke the colonies' thirst for war.
But still, the adventure must go on.

Taion receives a call from Isurugi. Give Command
a visit next time you drop by Colony Lambda.

Taking on Isurugi's request, Taion and the party
protected Nami's home colony from Moebius.

Lanz seems interested in what the
Lost Numbers' training sessions are
like. Go to the City's training ground.

Lanz and the others took part in a mission to
liberate cradles alongside the Lost Numbers,
unexpectedly reuniting with Gessel in the process.

Investigate the transport at the
shelter.

You received a monster culling request from
Monica to secure the Material Storage Warehouse
at the Great Sword.

The City was attacked by Shania, now herself
a Moebius. The last the party sees of her
before she vanishes is her smile...

Colony 4 is running out of medical supplies.
Taion has a plan to solve it. Follow his lead.

Together with Ethel, the party brought back
medical supplies. Their respect for her bravery
in the face of any and all danger has only deepened.

Go and find a gemstone that Riku
will like as you make your way
through the Invidian Tunnels.

During your gemstone hunt, Riku and Manana
found a way to fight together as a pair,
making them even handier than before.

Rest up at the Ruins of Seebu
Camp.

After hearing a Nopon speak of the
legendary Tanzoo's cuisine, Manana
decides to try and become his disciple.

It turned out Tanzoo is a blacksmith, not a cook.
Still, it wasn't all for nothing, as Manana got a brand
new pot to make even more delicious meals with.

Have Manana prepare a meal
that will impress Tanzoo.

Hand over the collected ingredients
to the legendary chef.

Lambda uses the Invidian Tunnels to mine ether.
Unfortunately, there's been a cave-in. Go check
it out.

First a cave-in, then Auto-Levs gone berserk...
As thanks for resolving both issues and protecting
Lambda, Isurugi accepts Taion's request to join the party.

Work together to remove the
boulder blocking the way.

Looking to refresh himself, Isurugi sets out in search
of something called a "spa". Go to the City to find
out more.

The party and Isurugi discovered a natural spa in
the Brasa Geothermal Belt. It appears Isurugi had
a refreshing time in the process.

Gather enough "About Natural Spas"
info fragments.

Suddenly reunited with the party, the party invite
Kamunabi to live on his own terms. Safety can
be guaranteed in the City, for the time being.

After so many twists and turns, Ethel and Kamunabi
decided to live on and survive together. Perhaps this
is fate at work?

Search for Ethel around
Centrilo Parade.

Curious about the man who gave them the
opportunity to choose a different life, the party
decide to go and ask Monica about Guernica.

The bereaved witnessed the off-seeing ceremony
and thanked the party for everything they've done.
Monica will lend you her help from now on.

Go to Michiba Canteen to hear out Monica, who
doesn't see eye to eye with Garrett or the Ouroboros
candidates.

Monica commands the City in her role as Elder,
with a firm plan to secure her people's future, but
the candidates seem to see things differently.

After climbing up a cliff that continues on
to the Great Sword, the party fends off a
Levnis-backed force.

With the Colony 30 Flame Clock destroyed,
Rudi's fight to protect everyone began in earnest.
He also vowed to help you, his new friends.

Lieutenant Yuzet has collapsed from overwork.
To fulfill his duty as his commander, Rudi decides
to head to Colony Lambda.

Exploring beyond Colony 30, Rudi realized that
the world has many moving parts to it, just like
a Levnis. This insight will fuel much growth.

Rumor has it that a raid on Colony 9 is planned.
If true, it can't be ignored. Go there, and help
your comrades.

Through helping him escape the bondage of Moebius,
Noah formed a deep bond with Zeon. He will make
for a very capable ally.

Due to the crop field issues and the emetaters, Zeon
has found himself in a bind. Help him and Colony 9
weather the storm.

In the midst of splendor and evolving challenges,
Zeon was not only able to establish new crop fields,
but also build a precious sense of camaraderie.

Find other fields in and around
Colony 9.

Gather 10 Spongy Spuds
in Morukuna Wildwood.

Plant the seed potatoes
in the fields.

Examine the Spongy Spud leaves,
and pluck the spuds out.

Defeat Commander Niina, and capture
Colony Iota.

The party bore witness to Niina's ingenuity for
survival and got a glimpse of her situation. They
agree to keep her being a sixth-termer top-secret.

As Colony Iota holds a tech summit with Colony 30,
the previous loss lingers in Niina's mind. Some
mediation between the colonies is required.

Niina's pain and true feelings came to light, and
real bridges of trust were built between Colonies 30
and Iota. Healthier relations now seem possible.

As the party move through Morukuna Wildwood,
they are ambushed by Agnian Soldiers, defeating
them.

Colony Tau's Flame Clock is no more.
To help Tau evolve and grow, Yuzuriha
decided to join the party.

Upon returning to Colony Tau, the party find
the Consul, who defeated the monsters, waiting
for them... Hear her out for now.

Colony Tau's strange modus vivendi was shown
to be their Consul's design. The whole affair has
once again reminded Yuzuriha of life's harshness.

On the Erythia Sea, the party finds itself going
head-to-head with a Moebius who goes by the
name of Triden.

Triden had long wanted to free his friends from the
Flame Clock's grip. The party, though initially
reluctant, have let him join their ranks.

Triden recalls how someone handed something to him
about 100 years ago. Go and look for it if you like.

What Triden had been looking for turned out to be
a jar of miso. Use this fabled ingredient to make 
Manana's Miso Soup.

The party find Mashiro attempting to single-handedly
repel a Kevesi raid on Colony Mu. Unable to stand
idly by, Noah and co. offer her their assistance.

Through her dramatic parting with Ichika,
Mashiro has gained much strength. Hoping to
learn more about Moebius, she has joined the party.

Help Mashiro save the people of
Colony Mu.

Gather enough "Colony Mu
Investigation" info fragments.

Distrust is growing in Colony Mu toward Mashiro,
who feels unable to tell them the truth about
Ichika. Help her regain the colony's trust.

Having finally told her colony the truth about Ichika,
Mashiro now accepts her for who she really was, and
has taken a big step forward, toward the future.

A mysterious girl appeared, piloting a fearsome
Levnis. Just who is this person...?

The dark fate surrounding Colony 0 has been lifted
thanks to Sena and the Ouroboros. No. 7, or
Nagiri, now ponders the meaning of freedom.

Vacant room in Caelum Residential
Quarter

At Nagiri's request, Sena and the party head to
Colony Lambda to get ingredients to make onigiri
for the people of Colony 0.

Having been reunited with No. 13, Nagiri finally saw
the path she must take. She will forever be thankful
to Sena for her kindness.

Locate the site of the attack
in the Dannagh Desert area.

Some Lost Numbers were attacked by a giant
monster in the Fornis region. Go with Ghondor
to investigate.

The big Tirkin was pushed into battle, defending
his children to the very last. Ghondor decided to
look after them in their father's place.

The party make an unusual find in Millick Meadows,
bringing them into conflict with an unidentified man,
who was searching for the same thing.

The mysterious man gave you his name: Gray. He also
seemed to know that Noah and co. were Ouroboros,
and ultimately offered them his help.

Some Lost Number hardliners are
up to something. Work with Rozana
to stop their scheme.

Thanks to Rozana's wits and Gray's skills,
the hardliners' scheme was foiled.

The party search for the highest location in Aionios
for Nia, who wishes to be closer to the skies.

With the future now safe in the party's hands, Nia
wished to travel together with them once more, until
such a day as their journey would come to an end...

While Melia was out with the party, various problems
arose at the Castle. Continue to work together with her
to resolve the issues.

With the City's hearts and minds put at ease,
Colony 9 having received support, and Agnian
opposition quelled, Melia officially joined the party.

Colony 9 has requested backup following
a recent Origin attack. Go there with Melia.

By helping out those caught in the landslide,
Melia showed the Colony 9 soldiers how a true
Queen should act.

The Agnian troops Aizel provoked have rallied
together to become a rebel force. Go to Agnus
Castle to discuss and resolve the issue.

Despite a minor scuffle, Melia was able to open a
dialog with the Agnian rebel force. She persuaded
them of the importance of mutual survival.

Melia receives a request from Monica asking her to
offer some words of encouragement to the City.
Head there together with her.

Talking to the various people of the City,
Melia helped to calm their fears, and prepare
them for what is to come.

Colony 9's new Sender appears to be struggling
with some problems. Try asking the people that
know him what's troubling him.

Url came clean to Colony 9 that he is no longer
able to perform as an Sender. He seems a little
more at peace now, at least...
Return to Carrie at Viliera Hill.

Colony 9 faces a supply shortage. Find reusable
things on the old battlefields to send back to Camilla.

The shortage was alleviated, for a while.
But there are soldiers, like Kite, who don't
approve of these methods.

Gather some supplies on the
old battlefields.

Fox might be raiding nearby colonies to solve the
food shortage. Gather intel, and then stop him.

You convinced Fox not to raid the nearby colonies,
but the shortage still needs to be solved somehow.
Find Fox by the Colony 9 Canteen.

Pursue Fox, and convince him
to come back to Colony 9.

Dissenting against Zeon's leadership, Kite and his
friends leave Colony 9. Ask Fox for details, and then
bring them back.

Kite and his friends reflected again on their freedom
from the Flame Clock, and decided to return to
Colony 9 to work together with Zeon after all.

Raising Spongy Spuds has put an end to Colony 9's
food shortages. Now go and spread the good word
to the other colonies!

The Spongy Spuds have made their way to Colony 4,
but Colony 9's mission to end food-supply-related
conflict has only just begun.

The Spongy Spuds have made their way to
Colony Mu, but Colony 9's mission to end
food-supply-related conflict has only just begun.

Make a Spongy Spud supper at the
Colony 4 Canteen.
Go to the Colony Mu fields.

Make a Spongy Spud supper at the
Colony Mu Canteen.

Leonardo's friends were killed by monsters while on a
mission. Head to Sonata Saddleback to see them off.

With Jango, Olivia and Marlon seen off, the
burden in Leonardo's heart was slightly eased.

Noah recalls a container that got blown off-course
before it could be recovered. With Colony 9 short
on supplies, now is a good time to go look for it.

The party found the unrecovered container and gave
it to Trish. There's still a way to go until the shortage
is resolved, though.

The party found the unrecovered container and
delivered it to Camilla. Hopefully, it will mitigate
the shortage somewhat.

Leonardo and Eastman appear to have fallen out about
something. Go and ask Leonardo what happened.

Marlon's hidden equipment didn't prove to
be the solution to Colony 9's problems...

Eilis hasn't returned to Colony 9. She might have
gone somewhere in the area of Li Garte Prison Camp.
Find her and bring her back safe.

Eilis safely returned to Colony 9 in her repaired
Levnis. She looks forward to a reunion with Mwamba.

Search for Eilis around the
Li Garte Prison Camp.
Return to where Eilis's Levnis is.

Go to Colony Iota's Storehouse. It seems that
Niina wants to open up about colony affairs
in the hope of gaining the party's trust.

Collectopaedia Cards can now be used to send
supplies to other colonies. Niina and the
others consider it a worthwhile investment.

Use the Collectopaedia Card to
send over supplies to Colony 4.

Taion decides to help procure some supplies to
confirm the accuracy of Colony Iota's intel, though
is decidedly unimpressed by Fugen's attitude.

Fugen headed out for new horizons to live life
as he sees fit. Niina concealed her sadness
as she bid him farewell.

Falling into Suzukuro's trap, the party is left in
Dannagh Desert. Meet her, and get your supply
distribution authorization back.

The party got their supply distribution authorization
back. Content with the data, Suzukuro now eyes new
frontiers of research.

Due to sending other colonies lots of supplies,
Colony Iota itself is running short. See if you can
help them out with that.

Colony Iota's supply shortage has been mitigated.
The party also heard from Mikage about another
side of Niina's personality.

Nobody can seem to reach Kotori. Inquire around
Colony Iota for more information.

With encouragement from Kotori and the party,
Niina made public both her true birthday and
her real age of six terms.

It seems the Collectopaedia is experiencing issues,
with duplicate and unreadable posts. Find someone
with specialist knowledge and ask them about it.

Caught up in a cave-in, Sif used a Collectopaedia
Card to send an S.O.S., thereby expanding the card's
range of uses.

Work together to remove the
boulder blocking the way.

Collectopaedia Cards are being used in unexpected
ways among the liberated colonies. Help solve some
lingering issues with the system.

Niina's Collectopaedia Card scheme has begun
to connect people and colonies like never before.

In Colony Iota, soldiers who have contributed greatly
are rewarded on Harvest Day, but one of them seems
to be missing. Go find the soldier in question.

Upon finding Misaka, the party handed her the
tiara. The Harvest Day evaluation system
seems to have been Kotori's idea.

The party suggest that the baseless Colony 0 move
into Li Garte Prison Camp. Negotiate the proposal
with Ghondor first.

The party drove out the raging Prison Warden, and
recaptured the prison. It can now be entrusted to
Colony 0.

Infiltrate from the Vent Entrance,
and defeat the Prison Warden.

To make the former prison camp more livable, first
speak with No. 6, who manages the colony's supplies,
about how to go about the interior refurbishment.

Negotiating with Roon, No. 6 got the necessary
arrangements for refurbishment in order. It will
be interesting to see how the camp gets refurbished.

Find the Nopon in the
Vista of Rhonnar area.

The amount of monsters in the vicinity of the former
prison camp has increased. Work with Colony 0 to
clear them out.

The monster clean-up went great, but there seem
to be tensions between Nagiri's colony mates,
perhaps due to some complex circumstances...

No. 15 has shut himself in a Ferron unit. Worried
for his wellbeing, the party try to coax him out.

The continuing functioning of the Ferron units after
the Flame Clock's destruction was thanks to No. 15.
He is now having himself a well-deserved rest.
Speak with No. 15 one more time.

Having somehow created tension between herself
and No. 9, Sena ruminates over how they can
reconcile their differences...

No. 3 fully made up with No. 9 by getting
her Sender's flute fixed. But, No. 9 still
remains wary of Sena...

Ask someone what happened to
No. 9.
Go to where Colony 0 used to be.

Nagiri tells the party some info about old world relics
they collected earlier. No. 8 seems to know more.

After hanging up the restored painting in the
prison camp, the party see the children depicted in it
and feel a sense of both calm, and wonder...

Sena is asked to give new names to the citizens
of Colony 0. She decides to think back on past
events for inspiration.

Now with their own names, Colony 0's citizens took
their first steps into their new lives as "people", rather
than numbers.

The mysterious Levnises from earlier have returned.
The party are determined to take them down this
time, once and for all.

Relying on coordinated team attacks, the party
managed to fend off the Levnis squad. But...

In attempting to play the score she picked up
in the City, Mio discovers that it's unfinished.
Ask around in the City to find out who wrote it.

The partial score was written by Todoroki.
Noah, Mio and Todoroki's joint performance of
the piece left a melodious mark on the City.

Left to his own devices, Romero is likely to get
himself killed. Bring back a Jeweled Pebble
for the sake of his romantic relationship.

The all-too-honest Romero couldn't get permission
to marry his sweetheart. The poor lovers remain
star-crossed, burdened by their noble status.

Stories arise of a Colony 30 Nopon aspiring to
become an Sender. Go meet him and find out
his motivation.

His promise to Colony 30's previous Sender Radek
now fulfilled, See-Mee-Mee is on course to inherit
his role and become "See-Mee-Off".

A Colony 30 squad sent into Dannagh Desert hasn't
returned, and communications are down. Go there,
and check on their well-being.

Finding Erun's squad caught up in battle in Dannagh
Desert, the party ensures they can go home safely.

Rudi has been leaving all his commander-type work
to his lieutenant, Yuzet... See if there is a better way
to arrange all this.

Even getting phase two done required a massive
investment of work. Cooperate with Rudi and
Colony 30 to finish Dorrick.

The parts for Mechafriend have gone missing during
maintenance. Ask around to see if anyone knows
where they are.

After reflecting on what they did, Nitonito and
Ubebee joined the Dorrick project, which should
go that much more smoothly from now on.

Gather enough "Parts Gone Missing"
info fragments.

Pulipuli raises concerns when he comes up in
conversation with Ubebee. Find him hiding
in maintenance to discuss Mechafriend.

Pulipuli hindered the Dorrick project for Niina's
sake. But Rudi still forgave him, and they resolved
to work together on finishing Dorrick.

Colony 30 has run out of ether cylinders.
You'll need to procure over 2,000 of them
to restart Dorrick's construction.

By working together with other colonies, Colony 30's
ether cylinder shortage was solved. Construction has
moved on to phase seven.

Talk with Repapa about the Nopon
dispatch.

Count the ether cylinders gathered
by Colony 30's Nopon dispatch.

Dispatch more Nopon to increase
the cylinder amount to over 2500.

Dorrick project's phase nine is a live combat test.
Go to the Terra Wastelands to see Dorrick in action.

With the City mechanics' help, the live combat test
was a great success. Construction will move on to
phase ten.

Dorrick is finally complete.
Go to the Terra Wastelands to
take part in the grand unveiling.

Despite Pulipuli's underhanded wrecking of Dorrick
and Mechafriend, the bonds of trust within Colony 30
are now deeper than ever. Back to work!

Ven, a Colony 30 mechanic, seems to be collecting
Fourtune Clovers. Try finding out where best to
harvest them.

The party gave Ven what he was looking for, but it
seems he was more concerned about the Levnises'
wellbeing than the pilots'...

Colony Lambda's Iron Giant is out of commission,
which inconveniently puts its canteen out of use too.
Suggest a plan to the head of manufacturing.

With permission from all squad captains and the
commander, a new temporary canteen will finally be
set up. Once it's ready, check out what's cooking!

Lambda's Sender seemed to have gone to the Fornis
region through the tunnels, but no search party has
been sent out. In light of this, go look for him instead.

Shijima's Coming-of-Age was on the horizon. Although
he'd lost his goal in life, he decided for now to
return to Colony Lambda, for Moraine's sake.

Look for the missing Sender
in the Invidian Tunnel Facility.
Moraine at the U. Tunnel Facility

Colony Lambda's Auto-Levs still can't be restarted.
Talk to the head of engineering to find out why.

The party worked together with Kotora to return the
Auto-Lev to its normal functionality. Lambda's full
defensive capabilities have now been restored.

Lure over the Mine No. 3
enemy soldiers.

The supplies prepared for the battle with Colony 5
are at the Invidian Trail. Help with their recovery.

The supplies turned out to be a trap, but with
the party around, they were successfully retrieved
anyway.

All the ether Colony Lambda has been mining has
created a surplus. Talk with Kouju about how best to
use the extra resources.

After negotiations with Zozoka, an agreement was
reached to sell surplus ether at the Nopon Caravan.

Hotsuma is developing something to strengthen
Lambda's defenses. Go see how he's getting on.

Despite Hotsuma's invention being superb, Colony
Lambda's strict regulations nearly prevented it
from getting implemented.

Lambda's Sender appears to have met his end...
Go and see how Moraine is coping with it.

Kouju contrived the Lambda attack himself, with
the purpose of forcing a particular agenda.
How will the colony respond to this...?

Lambda is reeling in shock from the Kouju case.
Go with Isurugi to discuss it with the captains.

As Isurugi expected, the colony has started to change.
With less red tape to wrangle through, Lambda can
now think and act for itself.

An unease is spreading through Colony Mu. Mashiro
wants to see if she can do something to reassure
everyone.

Plenty of food was procured, but things got awkward
when Tallow and Ayase ended up in an argument.
Some time will be needed to heal the colony's unity.

Tallow's rep has worsened. To
resolve the discord in Mu, you
lend an ear to everyone again.

The lieutenant selection process
failed. Blaming her timidity, Mashiro
is determined to solve this herself.

Make contributions to Colony Mu
to get Point Stickers from Tallow.
The Future I Want to Spin

You've received a call for help from Tsumugi
at newly-independent Colony Mu. Go see if
she's safe.

Colony Mu's Armu ranch has been completed. Tsumugi
resolved to make her Armus the happiest ones around,
even as she grapples with the vicissitudes of life.
West of Colony Mu Main Gate

Ayase has a favor to ask of Mashiro and the
party. Head to the much livelier Colony Mu.

The requested training went off without a hitch.
Its unity now stronger, Colony Mu has taken
another new step forward.
Talk to Nico to start training.

Mu's gates have been improved. Go inspect them
to see if anything else can be done to help prevent
invasion.

Triden's shock visit was certainly very eventful for
everyone involved. But, Mashiro now has a new friend
in him.

With Mu united and helping each other out, Mashiro is
uneasy about how much less she has to do. Ask
Tallow if there's anything she can help out with.

Touched by what her precious friends' were
doing for her, Mashiro felt hope, and how its
light will never fade within her, no matter what.
Patrol the Colony Mu area by boat.

Clean up any debris around
Colony Mu.

The formerly-imprisoned Lost Numbers are
now able to go home to the City. The Castle
even kindly offers to lend a boat.

The returning Lost Numbers have
safely made it home. Ghondor and
Dana have remained in the Castle.

Let the Armory pilot transport you
to the City.

Unaware that Shiki is only trying to be kind, the
City folk find his behavior suspicious. Find out why
Shiki is acting like he is.

Aware of the truth of the Castle, Shiki was trying
to correct past wrongs. It looks like Ghondor believes
him too.

Both the Lost Numbers and Agnian soldiers in the
Castle seem very busy. Find out why from Shiki.

The ship with the provisions has set sail, but cannot
be contacted. Dana and the others on the ship could
be in danger...

Hand over the ether cylinders to
Dana.

Contact was lost with Dana and the others before
they could make it to Farview Cape. Go look for
them in the Erythia Sea.

The ship Dana was on was attacked by rebels.
The attack's mastermind, Ragzy, was stopped,
but Dana's life couldn't be saved...

Despite the Castle's liberation, there are still
some people left locked up in its prison.
Inquire into the reasons with internal security.

Satisfied after their fight with the
party, the three fiends joined Internal
Affairs' security force to work as guards.

Due to the discovery of extenuating circumstances,
all three of the fiends were freed, and will be put
to work guarding VIPs from now on.

It is said Touma was locked up for the crime of
mass murder. Why did he do it?

Touma fought in a Levnis to protect his comrades,
but the Consul jailed him for it. Understanding this
at last, Tsuyu freed him.

It is said Shuuri was locked up for
the crime of blowing up containers.
Why did she commit the crime?

The container Shuuri blew up was
actually a trap set up by the Consul.
Upon learning this, Tsuyu freed her.

It is said Jhodor was locked up for
the crime of wiping certain intel.
Why did he commit the crime?

Jhodor was locked up for wiping
fake intel the Consul had circulated.
Hearing this, Tsuyu freed him.

Shiki and co. are called to the
City. Ghondor says nothing bad
will happen, but not a word more.

The unfamiliar City culture enthralls Shiki
and his friends. He vows to fight not just
for his colony, but for all of Aionios.

Let the Armory pilot transport you
to the City.

Clear out the monsters lurking
around the decrepit Iron Giant.

The Iron Giant Hulk was rebooted so that it's
up and running again. You can now use the
newly-arrived Nopon Caravan's rest spot.
Monsters near the Iron Giant hulk

Ashera entrusts Colony 11 to the party. For starters,
meet each of the "Three Ravens", her squad leaders,
and get them on-side.

The party and Ashera bested the Three Ravens in
a fierce, all-out battle, and in doing so, finally got
them to recognize their strength.

Many of Fort O'Virbus's leaders-in-training
underestimate you. Show them beyond any doubt
that experience trumps simple knowledge.

Fred and the others learned that it takes
hard work and trial and error to make it.
Spar with them again sometime.

The Captain of the Guard is looking for
the party. Go and see what she needs.

As requested by Sigrún, the party trained with
the guards led by Heath and Vigne, teaching
them the value of cooperation.

Before heading to the Cloudkeep, the party decides
to first investigate Colony Omega.

The party destroyed Colony Omega's Flame Clock,
freeing Miyabi, Mwamba, and all the other soldiers
who were stationed there.

The commander of Colony 11, Ashera, invites
the party to join her on her personal battlefield.
They're not very excited about what's to come...

The party put an end to the fight with Colony 11,
but having learned the reason why Ashera fights
as she does, Eunie anticipates further trouble ahead...

Consul R has declared war on Colony 11.
Ashera has been awaiting this with rabid anticipation,
and now...the games can finally begin.

Having learned the truth about Ashera,
Eunie made a portentous vow with her.
Ashera seemed...touched?

Rendezvous with Zuoren, Easel and
Clad at the First Rouia Bridge.

Rendezvous with Zuoren, Easel and
Clad at the Colony 11 Training Pit.

The party and Zuoren's squad defended Lambda from
another Kevesi army. Zuoren and co. welcomed the
opportunity to see some action with open arms.

After hunting with Easel, the party
sat down to feast on their catch,
which was shockingly tasty.

Though remarkably numb to pain, a fight
with the party allowed Clad to finally feel
the hurt, just the way he had longed to.

Some soldiers have deserted from Colony 11.
Hurry to Morukuna Wildwood where they escaped to.

The deserters were secured. One can only imagine
what Knockheart has in store for them...

Ashera invites the party to a mock battle, but she
won't be taking part. Instead, she decides to coerce
someone else to join the party's side this time.

The party emerged victorious from the grueling
mock battle. Ashera and Shidou seemed to have
a strange kind of rapport...

Colony 4 is under threat from a large monster force.
The party decide to help them, while remaining wary
of meddling in their affairs *too* much...

Upon saving the lives of the soldiers from the
tactician squad, and confronting their leader Maxie,
the party find they had already been accepted.

Maxie, whom the party saved previously, asks them
to eliminate a certain three boss monsters. Ask his
subordinates for more details.

The party dealt with the boss monsters
wonderfully. There should be less of a
threat from monsters now.

A squad secretly dispatched to other colonies
was attacked by parties unknown and wiped out.
Search the site of the attack to find out who did it.

The attack had been carried out by Levnises
like the one previously encountered in Morukuna
Wildwood. The party must remain on high alert.

Losing Ethel has caused Bolearis to sink into a
deep funk. Go see how he's getting on.

As acting commander, Bolearis quickly gets to
work directing the captains. Colony 4 should
be just fine.
Go visit Laszlo who is in the Colony 4 Canteen.

The true culprit turned out to be Jeremy,
who deeply resents Agnus. Mio hopes one day
he'll put aside his grudges and choose peace.

Gather info in Colony 4 on the true
villain.

The procurement division is being
flooded by supply requests from
every department. Help them out.

The party got the supplies the
procurement division wanted. They
should be fine for supplies for now.

How do Agnian Levnises float? Work with Aym
from the maintenance and development team to
find out the answer to this curious question.

Thanks to the parts that the party gathered,
Aym gained a clue as to how Agnian Levnises
float. Wait for further information!

Aym is frustrated that his research has reached a
dead end. Acquire parts from the "Mechapod Carthegia"
to help get his research up and running again.

It turns out the secret to the Agnian Levnises' flotation
mechanism lies in energy conversion efficiency.
Could such technology help restart the Iron Giant...?

Search for the Mechapod Carthegia
in Lavi Sandbar.

A certain Nopon from maintenance and development
has gone missing. Ask M&D chief Dinzel to see if
he knows the errant Nopon's whereabouts.

Inspired by the party, Hamahama and
Drunk have left to see Aionios. Say hi
if you spot them on your travels.

An odd noise reverberating in the area is spooking
Hamahama and Drunk. Go find the source of it to put
their minds at rest.

The noise came from an airdrop container.
Since its contents were of no use to the duo, the
party were more than happy to take them instead.

Search for the source of the
mysterious noise.

Return to the broken supply
container.

Drunk is angry at Hamahama for giving him Glare
Aubergine, which he can't stand. Show him that
it can be a part of a delicious meal.

Manana's special recipe has helped Drunk appreciate
Glare Aubergine. Now with a properly full stomach,
he can finally make preparations to depart.
Smear the tree in Bubblesia nectar.

Drunk and Hamahama are arguing over who lost the
luggage. Find the luggage, then help them make up.

The thieves were a group of Merignas. The party
warned the duo to be more careful with their things.
Perhaps they learned their lesson this time!

Drunk is making fun of Hamahama, who is sure he saw
a big monster. Work together with them to uncover
the truth.

The big monster was real, all right. Having almost
become lunch, the duo learned firsthand that he who
fights and runs away will live to fight another day.
Where the giant monster was seen

Hamahama is out cold! Drunk is desperately hurrying
him over to Olesha back at Colony 4...

The duo have now resumed their world-trotting
adventure, which has really only just begun.

Hearing about some husks left abandoned by
Singbreeze Funnel, the party set out to try and
see them off.

The husks were soldiers who had fallen victim to
monsters. The party hope that they can now find
their peace.

Send off the husks by
Singbreeze Funnel.

Sigrún requests that the party escort Zuoren
back to the fort. Just what is the relationship
between those two...?

The party stopped the armed uprising inside the
Castle. Ignoring Sigrún's invitation to rejoin the Guard,
Zuoren left in search of his next battlefield...

Resolve the problem at Fort
O'Virbus.

Curious about the Lost Numbers' scavenger force,
the party decide to find them in the N'ohm Wetlands
and get to know them better.

The party got to know Kakitsubata. Furthermore, they
experienced a day in the life of the Lost Numbers,
and learned how they see things.

Miyabi and Manana decide to take part in the City's
customary cook-off. Can they go all the way and
win?!

Despite missing out on victory, Miyabi stayed true to
her cooking like Manana suggested, and deepened her
bond with the City folk.

Gather info about the
cooking contest.

Go and take the ingredients to
Michiba Canteen.

Colony Tau has its own peculiar customs. However,
since the last major battle, many of their comrades'
husks still lie where they fell...

Colony Tau's Sender, previous commander
and other fallen were seen off by Noah and Mio.
May their spirits rest in peace.

Now self-sufficient, the time has come for Colony Tau
to harvest its crops. The only issue is that they are
short of manpower. Go offer them your help.

The party witnessed how resourceful Colony Tau are
in hunting the spud-eating monsters for their meat
during the harvest festival, broadening the menu.

Amagi went out hunting despite his injuries, and
has now been found. Ask Gushin for more details.

Thankfully, Amagi was safe. The party tracked
the monster in his place. It did, however, manage
to flee to the lower levels.

Colony Tau gives the Tirkins provisions every year to
bolster their alliance. Ask Rouei for more details.

Colony Tau has renewed their alliance with
the Tirkins, and the bond holds strong. The Tirking
will continue to welcome Yuzuriha and the Tau folk.

Worryingly, contact has been lost with Saibara,
who was headed to Colony 4. Go see if she is
all right.

It seems that after being freed from the Flame Clock,
Saibara had a vision of the soldier who killed her
friend, and went to Colony 4 looking for them...

Eishi arrived at Colony Tau along with
some Nopon, which are a rare sight there.
Go check up on them.

The Sadadan Bros.' invention revolutionized Colony
Tau's lifestyle. Eishi decided to accept them into
the community.

Koto has returned from Colony Gamma, and
is now a specialist in making accessories. Go see
how she is doing.

Koto has begun selling accessories in Colony Mu.
This looks like it will make a big contribution
to Colony Tau.

Seri has borrowed an ether-detecting probe
from Colony Lambda. Go help him out.

Signs of ether were detected from the lower levels of
Morukuna Wildwood. Seri will now work together with
Nasori and Colony Lambda to develop Colony Tau.

It is said in Colony Tau that the Spring of Rhonnar's
water makes you stronger. Lanz and Sena want to
see if it's true. Go investigate the rumor.

According to Nasori's survey, the composition of
Rhonnar's Spring is just like that of Quarquaka's...
Thus dies another one of Colony Tau's superstitions.

New ninth-termers of Colony Tau traditionally
head alone to the lower levels to take part in the
"Hunt of Plenty". Ask Amagi about it.

The Hunt of Plenty is no more. His fallen allies'
memory in heart, Amagi has decided to move
forward, along with Yuzuriha.

Kyrie got separated from her
unit yet again. Bring her back
to Colony Gamma.

Commander Shidou of Colony Gamma
has accepted the party's vision of the future
and pledged to see it through together with them.

Gather info from the Colony
Gamma soldiers.

Head to the "good place" Teach
mentioned.

The newbies' training will end with large-scale
maneuvers on Everblight Plain. Head there.

Shidou and the party rescued Kyrie, and put an end
to the entanglement with a vengeful opponent,
thereby stamping out evil at its source.

Shidou has requested that the party teach the
newbies. Turn them into fine, worthy soldiers.

In the live battle maneuvers, the newbies went
through all they'd learned, and became fully
fledged soldiers, with bright futures ahead of them.

Foots's squad, who excel in combat, asked for
Eunie and Sena's guidance. Teach them what
they need to know.

Eunie got to know the newbies in a mock battle,
while Sena put them through unforgiving weight
training. Foots's squad's training was concluded.
Speak to Foots, Nagumo or Isora.

Taion enlists Noah as an assistant for the lecture
he's delivering to Ashihara's squad. Don't let the newbies
show you up, and show them they can trust you.

Noah won against Ashihara, but the result isn't what
matters, it's what's learned along the way. Keep up
the good work to win the newbies' trust!

Noah lost against Ashihara, but on the bright side, the
two seemed to get on well, at least. Perhaps with
further guidance you can gain their trust.
Talk to Ashihara, Omina or Sukune.

Sukune from Ashihara's squad asked for Noah to
teach her. As her senior in off-seeing, show her
how it's done.

With Noah's advice, Sukune put the hesitation born
from losing Mikura behind her, much to Izunome's relief.

The Colony Tau - Tirkin alliance has been dissolved.
As a result, you should anticipate their hostility
when you travel through Morukuna Wildwood.

Koto has begun selling accessories in Colony Mu.
It certainly won't be easy for her, but hopefully she
should manage all right.

The party saved Amagi from the Tirkins. His fallen
allies' memory in heart, Amagi accepts the need to
move forward with Yuzuriha.

Lanz finally got a request to teach
a lesson! Show Kamuki what a
good, dependable teacher he is!

The party took part in Kamuki's
research. Despite teaching nothing,
Lanz seemed happy enough.

Thanks to a rigorously impartial lottery, Mio will be
teaching Kyrie, although what she is actually hoping
to learn about is a cause for concern and intrigue...

Kyrie was worried about what kind of leader she
should aim to be, but regained some confidence
thanks to Mio. She's sure to grow as a captain now.

Isora secretly wishes to become a
medical practitioner. Invite Colony 4's doctor,
Olesha, to support her in her studies.

Replacing Olesha, Maybach hit it off immediately
with the studious Isora. She won't have any
problems qualifying as a doctor at this rate.

Apparently, there is an artist at
Fort O'Virbus. Go meet him.

Seeing his painting praised by the City, Stefano
regained his confidence. If you're ever in need of
some G, try selling one of his paintings in the City.

Bring a model who will fit Stefano's
next painting, then talk to him.

Inspector Ulrich wants to check in on the colonies
that the party liberated. Guide him through the
liberated colonies.

Ulrich settled down in Agnus Castle to understand
further how the City, Keves, and Agnus might find
a way to coexist.

According to guards Heath and Vigne, dissidents
in the Castle are plotting something. Go to the ether
mine to investigate.

No hard evidence was found, but pay close attention
to any suspicious activity from the inspector.
Gather info by the Ether Mine.
Gather info by the storage area.

The inspector was allegedly seen in the basement
storehouse at night. Go to the storehouse, and
uncover the truth.

The party put a stop to Inspector Lucione's plot.
As a result, Ulrich now feels that coexistence
between Agnus and the City is an absolute must.

Send off the husks to the west
of the Tree Hollow Opening.

The party is invited by some City kids to help solve
a riddle. Search for what is "at foot of 15 light".

It was Azalea who created the riddle. After some
sad, difficult times, she kept her distance from people,
but now, she seems to have made some new friends.

Something called "novels" seem to be very
popular in the City. Go to Wellwell's store
to see if you can buy one.

Whatever the retrieved relics were used for, they've
given Lienda the spark of inspiration she needed to
let the words flow again!

It turns out Gray is a member of the
Lost Numbers. Go meet his partner
who is in the City, waiting for him.

The party helped Gray out with his partner's request.
It seems Rozana has quite a lot to do with Monica,
Samon and the Six Houses as well...

Young Shino of House Ortiz has sent the party
a rescue request. Go look for Hirachi's squad at
Cape Arcaphor in the Erythia Sea.

Hirachi tactfully welcomed the Colony 15 soldiers to
the City. It didn't take Shino long to take a shine to
the soldiers who saved his father's life.

The City folk are worried that Moebius
know where the City is. Ask Monica and
Travis for more details.

Kazami had hoped to survive Moebius by isolating
himself from the City, but Monica managed to
get him to reconsider.

Go see Romero and Joulietta to find out
if their marriage talks have
progressed any further.

In exchange for being disowned by
House Doyle, Joulietta can now be
by the side of her beloved Romero.

Upon finding a poorly-looking old
woman in the City, the party decide
to hurry her to the Medical Facility.

The sudden change of environment
has left some City folk feeling unwell.
The medicine should help with that.

The City children appear to be
planning something in Ribelly
Square. Go and see what's up.

The kids were making an accessory
as a present to give the Ouroboros.
Repay them by defeating Moebius.

Bring together all seven of the Nopon who wield
Ultimate Hammers, and they will fuse Origin shards
together for you, and upgrade the party's Blades.

All seven legendary Nopon have finally gathered
together in one place. Collect the Origin shards,
and then talk to Samon to upgrade the Blades.
The Key to a New Home

The City's Coming-of-Age has been called off this
year. Ask the members of the Six Houses and
this year's Homecomers why.

The City's Coming-of-Age was held successfully. Even
those who usually can't help but bicker with each
other were united in congratulating the Homecomers.

Search for Nopon that hold an
Ultimate Hammer.

Shillshill has asked you to confirm names and
bring back stones from Nopon belonging to each
caravan. You can take your time with this one.

The stones' purpose was to determine what
relationship the caravan Nopon would have with
humans. Some progress has surely been made.

The party finds a collapsed Nopon
Merchant in Eagus Wilderness. Help
rehydrate the poor thing.

Koma has been fully rehydrated.
He's going to the Hillside Iron Giant
Hulk, where Shillshill is waiting.

Past the strange cave filled with mechanical
contraptions, the party finds a bizarre Nopon
named Tagane. See what has got her so excitable.

The party learned that Tagane hid Nopon Coins
in all corners of the world. If you find any, give
them to Seekseek for some nice rewards.

Deep in Morukuna Wildwood, the party encounter
a mysterious Nopon. Accompany her.

Gin guided the party through Morukuna Wildwood.
Until the day when seven anvils ring, she will
remain in the garden.

The white fog that troubled Noah and co. has been
implicated in a string of disappearances around the
Erythia Sea. Get to the bottom of the matter.

The white fog was coming from monsters in
Anu Shoals. With the beasts taken care of,
no soldiers should go missing any more.

Go to "the two trees" as understood from the
wood pieces that washed up in Colony Mu,
and save whoever sent the message.

Nilni was not in distress after all. On the contrary,
he found a sense of romance in continuing his map-
making endeavor in the face of annihilation events.

The party find a curious monument somewhere
in the Erythia Sea. Your Nopon companions are
leery of making an offering to it... But why?

The "unspeakable being" Riku and Manana were
so afraid of turned out to be an adorable monster,
no more.

Gotsugotsu lost all three of his stones
while busy with prison labor. Look for them
in Li Garte Prison Camp's Perimeter Woodland.

The stone search was successful.
Gotsugotsu entrusted the party
with a stone to give to Shillshill.

Walk around the City, and see how
the Colony 15 soldiers are adapting
to their new environment.

It became obvious that the Colony 15 soldiers
will still need some more time before they get
fully used to life in the City...

The Colony 15 soldiers seem to have
gone missing from the City. Stop by
Michiba Canteen to find out more.

Thanks to the Colony 15 soldiers' sterling work
as soldiers of the Lost Numbers, Triden has been
given permission to enter the City.

Find a Bright Fig in Morukuna
Wildwood, and take it to Triden's
drinking buddy, Jougo.

Unfortunately, Jougo died as you
were searching for a Bright Fig,
leaving Triden with one fewer friend.

Gather enough "Saibara at
Colony 4" info fragments.

Head to the spot in the Erythia Sea
shrouded in white fog.
Renge at Colony Mu Hidden Coast

Follow Maxie's instructions, and ask
Yorde for information on one of the
monsters threatening the colony.

You have eliminated the monster that
Yorde indicated. You can report back
to Maxie once all is done.

Follow Maxie's instructions, and ask
Flauren for information on one of the
monsters threatening the colony.

You have eliminated the monster that
Flauren indicated. You can report back
to Maxie once all is done.

Follow Maxie's instructions, and ask
Jeremy for information on one of the
monsters threatening the colony.

You have eliminated the monster that
Jeremy indicated. You can report back
to Maxie once all is done.

Go to Colony 4 Command and
announce your departure.

Retrieve the supplies requisitioned by Polu
from the salvage corps.

The supplies have been retrieved safely.
Let's be sure to use them for all their worth.

The team that was to rendezvous with Laurea
has gone missing in action. To find them, head
for Shark's Jaws Cape.

You've saved the team's hides.
That should set Laurea's mind at ease.

Search for treasure at the
Cay of the Trick Grotto.

Search for Bright Figs in
Low Morukuna Wildwood.

Talk to Seekseek and trade in
Nopon Coins for items.
Make an offering at the monument.
Ask Nico to restart the training.

Investigate the mysterious light that has appeared
on the banks of Llyn Nyddwr in the Fornis region.
(You can get there starting partway through chapter 3.)

The Nopon Archsage you met in that puzzling place has
tasked you with completing a series of challenges.
Rise up to the occasion to get your hands on his prizes!
Investigate the light at Llyn Nyddwr.

Head to the Great Idalla Ravine to make the
acquaintance of a new Hero.
(You can get there starting partway through chapter 3.)

Ino, an artificial Blade, has become the party's ally!
Continue to gather High Ether and make Ino stronger
to further her ambitions.

Harvest High Ether from the
Ether Sphere.

Ino requires the party's help to defeat the Nopon Eater,
the monster threatening Nopon peace and prosperity.
Do it for the Nopon!

Ino and the party valiantly slew the Nopon Eater,
but the fight for Nopon love and peace will continue
for as long as Noponkind exists.

In order to upgrade their HD Ether Cylinders+,
the party decides to visit Sunny and Cheerio's
caravan.

The HD Ether Cylinder+ model was upgraded
without a hitch! Totoma also seemed willing to upgrade
it further, provided you could supply the materials.

Give Totoma the necessary materials
to upgrade the HD Ether Cylinder+.

Head to Serene Square to make the
acquaintance of a new Hero.
(You can get there starting partway through chapter 5.)

Sensing an opportunity for collaboration, Matia and the
party entered into an exclusive contract. Be sure to take
advantage of her accessory-crafting services sometime!
Craft an accessory at the City Camp.

It seems that the Archsage occasionally comes up
with something new...
(You must complete "Challenge Battles!" first.)

The Nopon Archsage has more trials up his sleeve yet!
Be prepared to tackle the new Archsage's Gauntlet he
came up with to keep him smiling wide and bright!

Complete any one Time Attack
challenge.

Matia has asked the party's help fulfilling Jake and
Tiian's order. Don't let her down!

With the party's help, Matia had no trouble crafting
elegant keepsakes for Jake and Tiian that met their
expectations, marking another victory for the arts.

Gather enough "Jake and Tiian"
info fragments.

Matthew and A are traveling through the
Cent-Omnia region in pursuit of their goal.

The two Moebius were slain by Matthew and A's hands.
With Nikol and Kagiroi freed from the Flame Clock's
bondage, what awaits our party in the days ahead...?
Look for a place to rest.

Head in the direction of the signal,
as indicated by the X-Reader.
Press on in search of City survivors.

Bring him any Nopon Medals and he'll gladly

In order to find a prime location for her dungeon,

Apparently, it's going to take one hundred years before

Help Saomi and Hyzen find the place

You located the treasure, but to Saomi's utter dismay,

Help Jethro out by collecting the

You gathered the soldiers' personal effects and fought
off the enemy squad. Jethro is to return to Colony 9,

Join Kayleigh in a search for the lost Harby.

His doubts at last dispelled, Harby vows to stand
by Kayleigh, come what may. Their true journey is

Decode the mysterious wall mural's message

The relic that was hidden in the final location

You successfully provided the required battle data,

"I lost my wedding ring somewhere in
Colony 9. If my wife finds out, I'm dead.
Please, I beg you, someone find it."

"Thanks so much for finding it! Sadly, my wife saw
the post on the noticeboard anyway, so I still ended
up having to sleep on the futon..."

"I saw a school of Krodlaxes swimming around

out so we can have fresh fish to eat!"

"Thanks for taking that on! Thanks to you,
everyone got to eat their fill of fishy treats."

"I think a rare kind of Shoox is nesting in the

"Thanks for taking out that Shoox! Those twin
glowy 'stache-frond-things will provide me plenty
of research material!"

"I hear an unusual Kapiba was seen at

purely for science, it would be appreciated!"

"Thanks for taking out that Kapiba!

HOW are they so fluffy? I MUST KNOW!"

"I dropped my book while on expedition to

"Thanks for bringing back my book! I was so excited

"Could someone take down a few Quadwings

"While exploring Zalmor's Thawtunnels, we

"Thanks for taking down the Vvarga for me! Being able
